<subSubSection pageId="162" pageNumber="765" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="162.[88,1295,265,687]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[89,200,298,332]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765">Habitat.</emphasis>
Secondary forest and scrubby habitats, including banana plantations and garden shrubs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[90,1041,381,410]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="162.[88,1295,265,687]" box="[90,1041,381,410]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[90,351,381,410]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
Diet includes vegetable matter and ground nuts.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[90,1142,420,449]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765" type="breeding">
<paragraph blockId="162.[88,1295,265,687]" box="[90,1142,420,449]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[90,224,420,449]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765">Breeding.</emphasis>
There is no well-defined breeding season. Embryos number 1-6.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="162" pageNumber="765" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="162.[88,1295,265,687]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[88,323,460,489]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Albertine Rift Thicket Rat are nocturnal and arboreal, although they are often caught on the ground.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[90,1029,535,569]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="162.[88,1295,265,687]" box="[90,1029,535,569]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[90,790,535,569]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[90,1180,574,608]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="162.[88,1295,265,687]" box="[90,1180,574,608]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[90,439,574,608]" pageId="162" pageNumber="765">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Near Threatened on The IUCN Red Lust.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
